s concerned. In the same year on November 6th-7th, the first session of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation Ministerial Meeting held in Canberra. -31 Days on July 29, 1990, the Second Ministerial Conference held in Singapore. Foreign Affairs and Trade Minister of Australia, Brunei, Canada, Indonesia, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, New Zealand, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and the United States and other 12 countries attended the meeting. After repeated consultations with the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC), based on the principle of \"one China\" and \"the difference between the sovereign state and regional economy,\" November 1991, China and Chinese Taipei and Hong Kong \"At the same time joined the agency. <br> 1991 11, 12-14, 2011, the Third Ministerial Meeting of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) held in Seoul. China, Chinese Taipei and Hong Kong for the first time to participate in the meeting, so that the total number of members to 15. The meeting adopted the \"Seoul Declaration on Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation, emphasized the significance of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation, and provides that the purpose of the organization of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation, the scope of activities and cooperative way. The meeting also adopted a statement urging promote the Uruguay Round of multilateral trade negotiations. (TodayinHistory.cn 10-11) <br> in 1992, at the Fourth Ministerial Conference in Bangkok by the \"Bangkok Declaration\" and \"Bangkok Joint Statement\", decided to set up a secretariat in Singapore, as permanent establishment of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC). This marks the conference the institutionalized nature by the Forum to organized a major step forward. The meeting also decided to further promote and expand regional trade liberalization efforts, and coordination and cooperation for trade and investment data, trade, technology transfer, human resources, energy, marine resources, communications, tran